                <p>
                    <h5>Will vuln.pub always notify me of every vulnerability all the time forever?</h5>
                    No. The idea is to make notification of vulnerabilities easier, but this will not catch everything. Don

                    <h5>Stop spamming me!</h5>
                    Sorry! If you get a false positive, send an email (see below) and I'll look into what happened.

                    <h5>What happens if versions in my manifests are garbage?</h5>
                    You might notice some versions you give get converted to have wildcard values. In the case where you have package "foo" in your monitor, with version "bar", clearly "bar" is not a valid version, so this is transformed into a wildcard. If a vulnerability is reported for "foo" with any version, you'll be notified.


                </p>
